  "prompt": "How do you find out what your zip code plus four is?",
  "response": "There are several ways to find out your Zip+4 code:\n\n*   **Use the USPS Website:** The most reliable method is to use the official USPS (United States Postal Service) website. They have a Zip Code Lookup tool. Enter your address, and it will provide your full Zip+4 code.\n\n*   **Look at Mail You've Received:** Check any mail you've received at your address. The Zip+4 code is often printed on the address label.\n\n*   **Online Search Engines/Mapping Services:** Many search engines or mapping services (like Google Maps, Bing Maps, etc.) will show the Zip+4 code when you enter your full address. However, double-check the information with the USPS website for accuracy.\n\n*   **Contact Your Local Post Office:** If you're still having trouble, you can contact your local post office directly. They should be able to provide you with your Zip+4 code.",
